This paper deals with social media analysis, specifically identifying communities within a larger network of social interactions on Twitter. The paper also mentions the use of ensemble community finding, which falls under the category of social network analysis. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.SD (Software Engineering). The paper also involves natural language processing and text analysis to identify topical communities, which falls under the category of information retrieval (cs.IR) and computational linguistics (cs.CL). Finally, the paper deals with social media and user behavior, which falls under the category of social computing (cs.SOC).
